<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="265" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. maculotegularis" pageId="0" pageNumber="265" rank="species" species="maculotegularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">A. maculotegularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov. is close to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. eous" pageId="0" pageNumber="265" rank="species" species="eous">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">A. eous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Semenov, 1935) but differs from the latter by the following characters: Tegula largely black; the lateral side of the first abdominal tergum yellowish brown; the 4th abdominal tergum with a small middle black macula; the middle and hind tibiae reddish brown; the first abdominal tergum with middle part distinctly produced; lancet with 51 serrulae, distance between the middle serrulae 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
breadth of a serrula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="265" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Holotype, female.</emphasis>
Body length 18.5 mm (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Color</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head and antenna dark yellowish brown, dorsum with a subquadrate black macula covering ocellar area, frons, inner half of inner orbit, lateral and middle foveae, clypeus and mouthparts largely yellow brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10C, E</figureCitation>
); thorax black, pronotum largely, anterior third of tegula, mesoscutellum, dorsum of metascutellum, posterior half of mesepisternum above carina and posterior half of katepimeron, posterior stripe of metepisternum yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10B, F</figureCitation>
); dorsum of abdomen black, lateral margin of tergum 1, 4th tergum except for middle triangular macula, 5th tergum almost entirely and middle third of terga 6-8 pale yellowish brown, lateral part of terga 6-8 blackish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10G, H</figureCitation>
), venter of abdomen dark brown, lateral macula on sterna 4-6 and sternum 7 yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10I</figureCitation>
); fore wing distinctly infuscate in anterior half, outer margin without narrow smoky macula, cells 2M, 3M, 2Cu and 2A largely subhyaline, veins and pterostigma pale brown; hind wing very feebly infuscate; legs largely yellowish brown, middle and hind coxae, trochanters and femora largely black (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265" start="Figure 10" startId="F10">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Figure 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yan &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2022" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Asicimbex" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Asicimbex maculotegularis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="265" rank="species" species="maculotegularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Asicimbex maculotegularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">A</emphasis>
female adult in dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">B</emphasis>
thoracic notum 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">C</emphasis>
head in dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">D</emphasis>
antenna 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">E</emphasis>
head in front view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">F</emphasis>
mesopleuron and metapleuron 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">G</emphasis>
abdominal terga 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">H</emphasis>
lateral side of abdomen 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">I</emphasis>
ovipositor sheath in ventral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">J</emphasis>
lancet 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">K</emphasis>
middle serrulae.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dorsum of head with minute punctures, clypeus largely smooth, with strong luster (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10B, C, E</figureCitation>
). Clypeus elevated, anterior margin roundly incised; labrum small and triangular, slightly broader than long; malar space 1.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of middle ocellus; postocellar area 2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long, middle furrow weak; lateral furrows distinct, divergent backwards; POL: OOL: OCL = 3: 5: 6; head behind eyes weakly enlarged (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10C</figureCitation>
); antenna 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head breadth, club breadth 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
apical breadth of antennomere 3, club length 1.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as antennomere 3 and 1.38 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
the combined length of antennomeres 4 and 5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10D</figureCitation>
), antennomere 3 as long as longest axis of eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Mesonotum densely punctured (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10B</figureCitation>
); scutellum strongly elevated with a broad and deep middle furrow, sparsely punctured; mesepisternum above carina densely but shallowly punctured mixed with microsculptures, oblique carina on mesopleuron sharp, mesepimeron largely polished, shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10F</figureCitation>
); cenchri elliptical, distance between inner margin of cenchri 2.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
the longest axis of a cenchrus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal tergum 1 minutely punctured mixed with microsculptures, without lateral smooth patch; lateral carina low but recognizable, anterior corner blunt, posterior corner roundish; posterior margin with broad and incision, bottom not round with obtuse middle process (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10G, H</figureCitation>
); middle process of sternum 7 narrow and triangular, basal breadth about 1/6 breadth of sternite 7; lance long and slender, subapical annuli clearly broadened, total length of annuli 5.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
height of 13th annulus, first annulus 1.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10J</figureCitation>
); lancet with 52 annuli and 51 serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10J</figureCitation>
), middle serrulae weakly narrowed toward truncate apex, each side with 4-5 large subbasal teeth, distance between middle serrulae 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
basal breadth of serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Asicimbex maculotegularis Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J lancet K middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707233" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">10K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
